VALUES ('ca05e5f2-8737-4800-99cd-77743a8dc7d9', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'The novelist''s early drafts, recently donated to a university archive, are crowded with elaborate descriptions of weather that never appear in the published book. Some scholars have read their absence as evidence that an editor pressured her to cut them. ______ her own marginal notes show that she struck the passages herself, convinced that the storms distracted from her characters'' quieter turmoil.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"In fact,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the marginal notes overturn the editor theory with a stronger, more direct counter-truth."},{"id":"B","text":"Therefore,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the final sentence contradicts the editor hypothesis rather than following from it."},{"id":"C","text":"Likewise,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''Likewise'' signals agreement, but the notes refute the scholars'' reading."},{"id":"D","text":"Accordingly,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''Accordingly'' marks a consequence of the prior claim, yet this sentence opposes it."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Identify the relationship
Scholars believe an editor forced the cuts, but the notes reveal {{yellow:she struck the passages herself}} for artistic reasons.
Step 2 — Why ''In fact'' follows
The sentence corrects the speculation with the actual evidence, intensifying the contrast; ''In fact'' introduces this corrective truth.
Distractor analysis:
- B: ''Therefore'' would make the self-editing a consequence of the editor theory, but it disproves that theory.
- C: ''Likewise'' implies the notes echo the scholars, when they contradict them.
- D: ''Accordingly'' signals a result that aligns with the prior claim, which is not the case.', 'Do the marginal notes confirm the editor theory or quietly demolish it?', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
